~ rockGF
Roquette: I look down at them every day. 
Roquette: They're so silly, wiggling their eyes. 
Roquette: I want them. I want to pet them.
- Is that appropriate?
	Roquette: I think that they desire it. I feel an [i]energy[/i] coming from them. They would make a nice pet.
	- But you're both rocks.
		Roquette: And yet they shall become my pet.
	- That sounds totally reasonable.
		Roquette: Mmm.
	=> END
		
- That sounds nice. Maybe I'll go back and pet them.
	Roquette: No! You shall not. They are mine.
	- What if they want both of us to pet them?
		Roquette: ...
		Roquette: I suppose that would be fine. 
		Roquette: We could make a calendar. 
		set States.roquette_pet = true
	- I sense... a deep underlying rage.
		Roquette: You do not understand its magnitude.
		- Clearly not.
		- I have some sense.
		Roquette: Leave me, child.
	=> END
=> END

